  "analysis": "You are in a shell session (root@...:/app). No SQL has been executed yet. There is no visible MySQL output or connection state in the terminal screen. Before issuing SQL statements to the database, we need to discover whether a MySQL server is present/running, whether the mysql client is available, and any local credentials (common locations: /etc/mysql/debian.cnf, environment variables, or .my.cnf). We may also search for .sql files or a database file to inspect. Nothing has been accomplished yet; the next steps are to detect the MySQL server/client and gather connection details so we can run SQL safely.",
